sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>Controller
    participant Online as Online Store Server<br/>6566/TCP (plain) or 6567/TCP (TLS)
    participant Offline as Offline Store Server<br/>8815/TCP (plain) or 8816/TCP (TLS)
    participant Registry as Registry Server<br/>6570/TCP (plain) or 6571/TCP (TLS)
    participant UI as UI Server<br/>8888/TCP (plain) or 8443/TCP (TLS)
    participant DB as Persistence Backend<br/>(Redis/PostgreSQL/SQLite/etc.)
    participant CronJob as CronJob Pod

    Note over User,DB: Flow 1: Feature Store Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>kubectl / RBAC auth
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (FeatureStore)<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployments, Services,<br/>PVCs, ConfigMaps, RBAC<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created
    Note over K8sAPI,UI: Kubernetes starts pods for<br/>Online, Offline, Registry, UI

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Online Feature Retrieval
    User->>Online: GET features<br/>HTTP/HTTPS port 80 or 443<br/>Auth: OIDC or K8s RBAC
    Online->>DB: Query feature values<br/>Protocol varies by backend<br/>Auth: Secret-based credentials
    DB-->>Online: Feature values
    Online-->>User: Feature response (JSON)

    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Offline Feature Retrieval
    User->>Offline: gRPC GetHistoricalFeatures<br/>port 80 or 443<br/>Auth: OIDC or K8s RBAC
    Offline->>DB: Query historical data<br/>Protocol varies by backend
    DB-->>Offline: Historical feature data
    Offline-->>User: Feature DataFrame (gRPC)

    Note over User,DB: Flow 4: CronJob Execution
    Note over CronJob: Kubernetes schedules CronJob
    CronJob->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec into<br/>Feast deployment pod<br/>Auth: RBAC (pods/exec)
    K8sAPI->>Online: exec: feast apply /<br/>feast materialize-incremental
    Online->>DB: Materialize features<br/>Auth: Secret-based
    DB-->>Online: Write confirmed

    Note over User,DB: Flow 5: Remote Registry Reference
    Online->>Registry: gRPC registry lookup<br/>port 80 or 443<br/>TLS (OpenShift auto)
    Registry-->>Online: Feature metadata
